BestSoFar.framework.core

Interface WorkflowContainer<I,O>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    ChildOf<Workflow<?,?>>, Deletable, Element<I,O>, EventuallyImmutable, ParentOf<Workflow<I,O>>, Processor<I,O>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractWorkflowContainer

    public interface WorkflowContainer<I,O>
extends Element<I,O>, ParentOf<Workflow<I,O>>
    A WorkflowContainer is an Element that contains one or more Workflow objects.

    When a WorkflowContainer is asked to process a Mediator, it must choose one of its Workflow children to perform the processing, so only one Mediator is returned.

    When asked to process a training batch, the WorkflowContainer must process each input Mediator with every Workflow that could conceivably process it, creating an output Mediator for each Workflow and for each input Mediator.
